      "content": "hey, i'm on a call with the representative from Apex Materials right now. they just asked me if we have any urgent upcoming requirements that would affect our negotiation or if we're looking at a steady volume over the next year. i know that internal memo said we're actually running dangerously low on their specific grade of alloy and might need a massive emergency shipment in two months... how should i answer this? i dont want them to jack up the price because they know we're stuck.",
